{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.18",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 18 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:1",
      "text": "He that hath a mind to depart from a friend, seeketh occasions: he shall ever be subject to reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:2",
      "text": "A fool receiveth not the words of prudence: unless thou say those things which are in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:3",
      "text": "The wicked man, when he is come into the depths of sins, contemneth: but ignominy and reproach follow him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:4",
      "text": "Words from the mouth of a man are as deep water: and the fountain of wisdom is an overflowing stream.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:5",
      "text": "It is not good to accept the person of the wicked, to decline from the truth of judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:6",
      "text": "The lips of a fool intermeddle with strife: and his mouth provoketh quarrels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:7",
      "text": "The mouth of a fool is his destruction: and his lips are the ruin of his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:8",
      "text": "The words of the double tongued are as if they were harmless: and they reach even to the inner parts of the bowels. Fear casteth down the slothful: and the souls of the effeminate shall be hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:9",
      "text": "He that is loose and slack in his work, is the brother of him that wasteth his own works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:10",
      "text": "The name of the Lord is a strong tower: the just runneth to it, and shall be exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:11",
      "text": "The substance of the rich man is the city of his strength, and as a strong wall compassing him about.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:12",
      "text": "Before destruction, the heart of a man is exalted: and before he be glorified, it is humbled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:13",
      "text": "He that answereth before he heareth, sheweth himself to be a fool, and worthy of confusion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:14",
      "text": "The spirit of a man upholdeth his infirmity: but a spirit that is easily angered, who can bear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:15",
      "text": "A wise heart shall acquire knowledge: and the ear of the wise seeketh instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:16",
      "text": "A man's gift enlargeth his way, and maketh him room before princes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:17",
      "text": "The just is first accuser of himself: his friend cometh, and shall search him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:18",
      "text": "The lot suppresseth contentions, and determineth even between the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:19",
      "text": "A brother that is helped by his brother, is like a strong city: and judgments are like the bars of cities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:20",
      "text": "Of the fruit of a man's mouth shall his belly be satisfied: and the offspring of his lips shall fill him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:21",
      "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue: they that love it, shall eat the fruits thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:22",
      "text": "He that hath found a good wife, hath found a good thing, and shall receive a pleasure from the Lord. He that driveth away a good wife, driveth away a good thing: but he that keepeth an adulteress, is foolish and wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:23",
      "text": "The poor will speak with supplications, and the rich will speak roughly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.18.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:24",
      "text": "A man amiable in society, shall be more friendly than a brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
